The technical term is DNS query logs or DNS resolver logs. In the context of Azure Firewall specifically they come from the DNS proxy feature, which means the firewall is acting as a recursive resolver for your VNet resources. The logs it generates are sometimes called DNS proxy logs in Azure's own documentation. All of these terms refer to the same thing — the record of what a client asked for and what answer they got back.

