How Does _Im_Dns() Know Which Tables to Look In?

It does not magically discover tables. It was hardcoded by Microsoft when they wrote the parser. A team at Microsoft looked at every data source that could produce DNS logs, wrote individual filtering parsers for each one, and then wrote the unifying parser to call all of them. So it only knows about sources Microsoft has explicitly built support for. If a client has a DNS source that Microsoft has never written a parser for, _Im_Dns() will never see that data.

