The Firewall DNS proxy logs in AzureDiagnostics are your primary detection surface. This is where you will catch the threats that matter most — a compromised VM trying to reach a known bad domain, DNS tunneling, beaconing, fast flux domains.

The Private DNS Resolver logs in DNSQueryLogs are supplementary. They give you visibility into internal traffic patterns, which matters for detecting lateral movement and insider threats, but they will not show you a device trying to reach malware infrastructure on the internet because that traffic goes through the firewall, not the resolver.

