A Microsoft-managed service running inside Azure whose job is to resolve internal private
names — resources that do not exist on the public internet. When an Azure VM needs to reach
a private database, a private storage account, or another internal service, it queries the
resolver to get the internal IP address. This is essentially the internal phone book for
Azure resources communicating with each other.

